    "explanation": "Use a hash map to store scores for each student ID. For each ID, sort the scores in descending order and take the first five. Calculate their average using integer division as per LeetCode requirements.",
    "answer": "def highFive(items):\n    d = collections.defaultdict(list)\n    for idx, score in items:\n        d[idx].append(score)\n    res = []\n    for idx in sorted(d.keys()):\n        top5 = sorted(d[idx], reverse=True)[:5]\n        res.append([idx, sum(top5) // 5])\n    return res",
